Runs all Layer 1 static/quality checks against a Rust workspace and is the single entry point both CI and the pre-commit hook invoke; takes an optional root directory (`$1`, default `.`) and `cd`s into it before running anything.

Its defining behavior is that it never short-circuits: every check runs regardless of earlier failures via the `RUN` helper, which captures each command's exit status into `OVERALL`, prints `OK:`/`FAIL: <name>`, and only exits non-zero (`OVERALL`) at the very end — so a single invocation always surfaces the full set of failures rather than the first one. `PHASE` just prints a section header; it carries no logic.

Checks run in order: `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy` (with `RUSTFLAGS="-D warnings"`, all targets/features), `cargo doc` (with `RUSTDOCFLAGS="-D warnings"`), `cargo deny check`, `cargo machete`, then four repo-local scripts resolved relative to the script's own directory via `SCRIPTS_DIR` (computed from `$0`, not from `$ROOT`): `rationale_check.py`, `workspace_lints_check.sh`, `no_allow_check.sh`, `cycle_check.sh`. Adding, removing, or renaming any Layer 1 check means editing this file's `RUN` list — it's the sole authoritative list of what "Layer 1" means. `rationale_check.py` and the three `*_check.sh` scripts must exist alongside this file in `scripts/`; the first four are passed `.` (the now-cd'd `$ROOT`) as an argument, `cycle_check.sh` is called with none, and `workspace_lints_check.sh`/`no_allow_check.sh` also take `.` as an argument — so those scripts' own argument-handling conventions must stay compatible with how they're invoked here.

Uses `set -uo pipefail` (no `-e`, deliberately, since failures must not abort the run).